---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout title="Home">
  <h1>Hexpunk</h1>
  <p>
    Hexagonal-first, wireframe-cyberpunk Lit component design system. See
    <a href="https://github.com/zeraphie/hexpunk/blob/main/DESIGN.md">DESIGN.md</a>
    for the full spec.
  </p>

  <h2>Spatial primitives</h2>
  <p>Three composable layouts that the rest of the system builds on:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>
      <code>&lt;hp-grid&gt;</code> — invisible axial coordinate space with drag, snap, and bond detection.
    </li>
    <li>
      <code>&lt;hp-cluster&gt;</code> — canonical 5-hex navigation rosette.
    </li>
    <li>
      <code>&lt;hp-tether&gt;</code> — curved bezier connecting two distant molecules across the canvas.
    </li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Quick links</h2>
  <p>
    Browse the side nav to jump into any atom or molecule demo. Each page lives at
    its own URL — cross-document View Transitions will eventually glue them together
    via <code>&lt;hp-unfold-page&gt;</code>.
  </p>
</Layout>
